---
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Live Demo — Graph-RAG in Action | EdgeQuake"
  description="Step-by-step EdgeQuake demo: ingest a document, inspect the knowledge graph, compare all 6 retrieval modes, and trace answers back to source material."
>
  <section class="py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mkt-text sm:text-5xl">
          Evaluate the EdgeQuake Workflow
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg mkt-text-muted">
          Use this page as the shortest path from first run to meaningful
          validation: ingest a document, inspect the graph, compare retrieval
          modes, and trace answers back to source material.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed mkt-text-dim">
          If you need installation details first, go to the
          <a
            href="/docs/getting-started/installation/"
            class="mkt-accent-text hover:underline"
          >
            installation guide</a
          >. If you want the production framing, continue to the
          <a href="/enterprise/" class="mkt-accent-text hover:underline">
            enterprise page</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr]">
        <div class="mkt-card rounded-xl p-8">
          <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-left">
            <div
              class="mkt-accent-surface mb-6 inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl"
            >
              <svg
                class="h-8 w-8"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <polygon points="13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2"
                ></polygon>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mkt-text">
              Interactive Demo Workflow
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 mkt-text-muted">
              The demo is a real EdgeQuake stack running locally. It is best for
              evaluating document ingestion, graph construction, and query
              behavior end to end rather than browsing a static placeholder.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed mkt-text-dim">
              This flow is useful for platform teams testing Graph-RAG quality,
              developers validating API ergonomics, and decision-makers who want
              to understand what the product actually does before reading deep
              technical documentation.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
              <div class="mkt-card rounded-xl p-5">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold mkt-accent-text">
                  1. Start services
                </div>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm mkt-text-muted">
                  Bring up PostgreSQL, the API, and the web UI with the standard
                  development workflow.
                </p>
                <div class="mkt-code-surface mt-4 rounded-lg p-3">
                  <code class="text-sm mkt-text-secondary">make dev</code>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="mkt-card rounded-xl p-5">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold mkt-accent-text">
                  2. Ingest a document
                </div>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm mkt-text-muted">
                  Upload a PDF or markdown source and watch chunking,
                  extraction, and lineage-aware processing complete in the UI.
                </p>
                <div class="mkt-code-surface mt-4 rounded-lg p-3">
                  <code class="text-sm mkt-text-secondary"
                    >http://localhost:3000/documents</code
                  >
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="mkt-card rounded-xl p-5">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold mkt-accent-text">
                  3. Query the graph
                </div>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm mkt-text-muted">
                  Ask the same question with different retrieval modes and
                  compare local, global, hybrid, and graph-aware answers.
                </p>
                <div class="mkt-code-surface mt-4 rounded-lg p-3">
                  <code class="text-sm mkt-text-secondary"
                    >http://localhost:3000</code
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
              <a
                href="/docs/getting-started/"
                class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg bg-accent-600 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-accent-500 transition-colors"
              >
                Getting Started Guide
              </a>
              <a
                href="/docs/tutorials/pdf-ingestion/"
                class="mkt-outline-button px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold"
              >
                PDF Ingestion Tutorial
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="mkt-card rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mkt-text">What to Validate</h2>
            <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm mkt-text-muted">
              <li>Document upload and processing state transitions</li>
              <li>Entity extraction quality and graph coverage</li>
              <li>Query-mode differences for the same prompt</li>
              <li>Source traceability from answer back to document</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="mkt-card rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mkt-text">Where to go next</h2>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm">
              <a
                href="/docs/tutorials/pdf-ingestion/"
                class="block mkt-text-muted hover:mkt-text transition-colors"
              >
                PDF ingestion tutorial for layout-heavy documents
              </a>
              <a
                href="/docs/concepts/graph-rag/"
                class="block mkt-text-muted hover:mkt-text transition-colors"
              >
                Graph-RAG concepts and retrieval model overview
              </a>
              <a
                href="/ecosystem/"
                class="block mkt-text-muted hover:mkt-text transition-colors"
              >
                Ecosystem and crate boundaries
              </a>
              <a
                href="/contact/"
                class="block mkt-text-muted hover:mkt-text transition-colors"
              >
                Contact the team for implementation help
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mkt-card rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mkt-text">
              Need the stack recipe?
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 mkt-text-muted">
              If you are evaluating the full experience, use the Makefile-based
              workflow instead of piecing services together manually. That keeps
              the ports, environment variables, and dependencies aligned with
              the docs.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
              <a
                href="/docs/getting-started/installation/"
                class="mkt-outline-button px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold"
              >
                Installation Guide
              </a>
              <a
                href="https://github.com/raphaelmansuy/edgequake"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="mkt-outline-button px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold"
              >
                View Source
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
